-- Provides the greatest control over hiring

-- Gives you the ability to define separate hiring rules and restrictions for each position 
 - You must specify the number of positions to fill
 - An open, approved position is required before you can hire, promote, transfer, or demote workers
 - Each position you create cn=an have its own definition and hiring restrictions

-- Use it when :
 - You need the ability to define each position narrowly based on the hiring location, job requirements and current needs and are subject to tight hiring controls
